    "Based on this default setting, we show how different RC designs can generally be interpreted as optimizing in one and/or multiple parts along the following directions.",
    "Firstly, in RC coupling parameter search, with the goal of selecting a good and potentially optimal coupling parameter γ to maintain the RC dynamics bounded and produces rich pattern that allow for the internal states to form a signal bases that can later be combined to approximate the desired series {z(t)}.",
    "Empirical studies have shown that γ chosen so that the system is around the edge of chaos 15 typically produces the best outcome, which is supported by a necessary but not sufficient condition -imposed on the largest singular value of the effective stability matrix W γ = (1 -γ) + γW.",
